{{Infobox military person |name=Berthold Graßmuck |birth_date=13 January 1917 |death_date={{death date and age|1942|10|18|1917|1|13|df=y}} |image= |caption= |birth_place= [[Bad Rodach]] |death_place= [[Stalingrad]], [[Soviet Union]] |nickname= |allegiance={{flag|Nazi Germany}} |branch={{Luftwaffe}} |serviceyears=?–1942 |rank=[[Oberfeldwebel]] |unit=[[Jagdgeschwader 52|JG 52]] |commands= |battles=[[World War II]] *[[Eastern Front (World War II)|Eastern Front]] *[[Battle of Stalingrad]] |awards=[[Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross]] |laterwork=}}
'''Berthold Graßmuck''' (13 January 1917 – 18 October 1942) was a [[Germany|German]] [[Luftwaffe]] [[fighter ace|ace]] and recipient of the [[Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross]] during [[World War II]]. The Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross was awarded to recognise extreme battlefield bravery or successful military leadership. Berthold Graßmuck was shot down by Soviet flak on 18 October 1942 over [[Pitomnik Airfield]] during the [[Battle of Stalingrad]]. During his career he was credited with 65 victories.
==Awards== * [[Aviator badge]] * [[Front Flying Clasp of the Luftwaffe]] * [[Ehrenpokal der Luftwaffe]] (6 July 1942) * [[Iron Cross]] (1939) ** 2nd Class ** 1st Class * [[German Cross]] in Gold on 13 August 1942 as ''[[Oberfeldwebel]]'' in the I./Jagdgeschwader 52<ref>Patzwall & Scherzer 2001, p. 146.</ref> * [[Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross]] on 19 September 1942 as ''Oberfeldwebel'' and pilot in the 2./Jagdgeschwader 52<ref>Fellgiebel 2000, p. 168.</ref>
